828
00:41:12,000 --> 00:41:13,300
Somebody stop him!

829
00:41:13,500 --> 00:41:15,000
Somebody call the police!

830
00:41:41,300 --> 00:41:43,300
-lt's fabulous up here.
-Beautiful.

831
00:41:43,500 --> 00:41:45,100
Look, a ferris wheel!

832
00:41:46,000 --> 00:41:47,600
-Look at the swings!
-Want to go?

833
00:41:47,800 --> 00:41:48,400
Yeah!

834
00:41:54,600 --> 00:41:56,000
Very good!

835
00:41:57,200 --> 00:41:58,600
Would you like this?

836
00:41:58,800 --> 00:42:01,600
Dad, high-five!

837
00:42:07,700 --> 00:42:09,200
You want some ofthis joint?

838
00:42:09,400 --> 00:42:11,300
No. l can't stand that stuff.

839
00:42:12,100 --> 00:42:13,800
You see that place there?

840
00:42:14,000 --> 00:42:15,400
That Red Apple Rest?

841
00:42:16,000 --> 00:42:17,100
Years ago...

842
00:42:17,300 --> 00:42:19,400
my then wife, Jane,
and l...

843
00:42:19,900 --> 00:42:22,600
were coming back from
her sister's house...

844
00:42:22,800 --> 00:42:24,000
and we had a fight.

845
00:42:24,200 --> 00:42:27,400
She had her period, and we
stopped to get water for Midol.

846
00:42:27,700 --> 00:42:29,300
l don't want a child!

847
00:42:29,600 --> 00:42:31,700
And don't bring it up
in front of my parents!

848
00:42:32,000 --> 00:42:34,800
-l don't understand.
-We've discussed it!

849
00:42:35,000 --> 00:42:37,100
-Don't l get a vote?
-You have a child!

850
00:42:37,300 --> 00:42:39,800
-Who l never get to see!
-That's not my fault!

851
00:42:40,100 --> 00:42:41,500
l like being a father.

852
00:42:41,700 --> 00:42:44,500
l'm not Lucy. You knew
that when you married me!

853
00:42:44,700 --> 00:42:47,100
So your work means no children.

854
00:42:47,400 --> 00:42:49,100
Since when are you a family man?

855
00:42:49,400 --> 00:42:52,200
Don't think l don't see
you staring at my sister Lucy.

856
00:42:52,400 --> 00:42:53,100
What?

857
00:42:53,600 --> 00:42:55,000
Don't play ignorant.

858
00:42:55,200 --> 00:42:56,800
You watch her walk and sit.

859
00:42:57,000 --> 00:42:59,000
You can't keep
your eyes off hertoes!

860
00:42:59,200 --> 00:43:02,200
Are you fucking nuts?
What are you suggesting?

861
00:43:02,400 --> 00:43:06,000
l wouldn't put it past you if you
wanted to have athing with her.

862
00:43:06,800 --> 00:43:09,100
She's a neurotic, suburban Hausfrau!

863
00:43:09,400 --> 00:43:11,600
l have no interest in her.
Zero. Nothing.

864
00:43:11,900 --> 00:43:14,200
You're level of denial
is a little intense.

865
00:43:14,400 --> 00:43:17,500
You're suffering from
a pre-menstrual nuclear meltdown.

866
00:43:18,700 --> 00:43:19,700
You want a hit?

867
00:43:21,100 --> 00:43:23,600
No. That smoke is killing me.

868
00:43:25,300 --> 00:43:28,000
l'm going to go to the bathroom.
Catch you later.

869
00:43:41,700 --> 00:43:43,800
Cold fish, your third ex-wife.

870
00:43:44,000 --> 00:43:46,000
She never would have made
a good mother.

871
00:43:46,400 --> 00:43:47,600
Who are you?

872
00:43:48,200 --> 00:43:49,900
lt's me. Ken!

873
00:43:52,600 --> 00:43:56,200
Look at this guy! You created me,
now you don't recognize me?

874
00:43:56,600 --> 00:43:59,200
l'm a little bit high because
of her smoke...

875
00:43:59,400 --> 00:44:01,400
How'd you ever
hook up with Jane?

876
00:44:01,700 --> 00:44:05,200
Jane was fine. Jane was just
having her period. She was...

877
00:44:05,400 --> 00:44:07,200
lt wasn't just her period.

878
00:44:07,400 --> 00:44:09,400
She was a cold, selfish woman.

879
00:44:09,700 --> 00:44:13,500
She's so self-involved she doesn't
realize her sister hates her.

880
00:44:14,100 --> 00:44:15,800
How do you know so much?

881
00:44:16,600 --> 00:44:18,900
l'm just you, thinly disguised.

882
00:44:19,200 --> 00:44:22,400
You gave me a little more
maturity and a different name.

883
00:44:23,200 --> 00:44:25,300
Are you saying that l knowthis?

884
00:44:25,500 --> 00:44:27,100
Yes!
That's why you picked her!

885
00:44:27,400 --> 00:44:30,000
So it wouldn't work, and you'd
never have to give up...

886
00:44:30,200 --> 00:44:33,700
sport-fucking and chronic
dissatisfaction and grow up.

887
00:44:34,000 --> 00:44:37,200
l won't stand here and get
lectured by my own creation.

888
00:44:37,400 --> 00:44:38,800
You can't fool me.

889
00:44:39,300 --> 00:44:42,300
l'm not your shrink.
He only knows what you tell him.

890
00:44:42,600 --> 00:44:43,500
l knowthe truth.

891
00:44:43,700 --> 00:44:45,400
And her sister, Lucy.

892
00:44:45,600 --> 00:44:47,000
Another head-case.

893
00:44:47,800 --> 00:44:49,400
You sure can pick them.

894
00:44:49,700 --> 00:44:51,500
But even she was better
than Jane.

895
00:44:51,800 --> 00:44:54,100
More maternal and she loved you.

896
00:44:54,500 --> 00:44:57,300
You weren't there the day your
bomb dropped on her...

897
00:44:57,600 --> 00:44:58,600
but take a look.

898
00:45:01,100 --> 00:45:02,300
He left me!

899
00:45:02,600 --> 00:45:04,500
Our marriage is finished!

900
00:45:04,900 --> 00:45:07,100
l'm sorry to hear that.

901
00:45:07,600 --> 00:45:08,700
You shocked?

902
00:45:08,900 --> 00:45:10,000
Yes and no.

903
00:45:10,800 --> 00:45:13,800
Things have not been very good
for some time.

904
00:45:14,000 --> 00:45:15,700
l knew he played around.

905
00:45:16,500 --> 00:45:18,600
Did you?
You never mentioned that.

906
00:45:18,800 --> 00:45:21,600
l don't like to discuss
my private life.

907
00:45:21,900 --> 00:45:24,800
First suspected Lynn, his editor.
Then l thought...

908
00:45:25,100 --> 00:45:28,300
it might be Allison Davis,
a friend of ours.

909
00:45:28,700 --> 00:45:31,400
l even thought he might have
a crush on you.

910
00:45:32,000 --> 00:45:33,000
Me?

911
00:45:33,500 --> 00:45:37,100
You're beautiful and we've spent
a lot oftime together...

912
00:45:37,400 --> 00:45:39,500
and you two get along very well.

913
00:45:39,700 --> 00:45:43,400
Obviously l knew you never would
in a million years...

914
00:45:44,100 --> 00:45:46,800
but l imagined he longed for you.

915
00:45:47,100 --> 00:45:50,700
l even heard him mention
your name in his sleep once.

916
00:45:51,800 --> 00:45:53,000
My goodness.

917
00:45:57,400 --> 00:45:58,700
That's absurd!

918
00:46:00,400 --> 00:46:01,800
Really!

919
00:46:03,000 --> 00:46:04,500
You're all red!

920
00:46:04,800 --> 00:46:05,600
No!

921
00:46:08,800 --> 00:46:10,000
Are you okay?

922
00:46:12,600 --> 00:46:14,800
Since we're talking openly...

923
00:46:16,000 --> 00:46:18,200
l have a confession to make.

924
00:46:19,000 --> 00:46:19,800
Yes?

925
00:46:23,300 --> 00:46:27,000
Life sometimes takes very
strange twists and turns.

926
00:46:27,300 --> 00:46:30,200
lt overwhelms us, and we can't
help our feelings.

927
00:46:30,400 --> 00:46:31,800
Our feelings are irrational.

928
00:46:32,000 --> 00:46:35,300
But to hear from your husband
that he found another woman!

929
00:46:36,800 --> 00:46:38,100
He said that?

930
00:46:38,300 --> 00:46:40,700
He said his future
is all mapped out.

931
00:46:46,200 --> 00:46:48,600
l'm going to be totally
frank with you.

932
00:46:48,900 --> 00:46:51,600
-Try to hang on and understand.
-What? l'm being replaced.

933
00:46:51,800 --> 00:46:53,600
But it doesn't have to be
a nightmare...

934
00:46:53,800 --> 00:46:56,000
ifwe're all just mature about it.

935
00:46:56,200 --> 00:46:58,200
Replaced by a 25-year-old.

936
00:47:00,000 --> 00:47:01,700
-Excuse me?
-A 25-year-old.

937
00:47:01,900 --> 00:47:05,400
A wanna-be writer. Fay Sexton is her
sexy name.

938
00:47:07,700 --> 00:47:10,000
What's the matter?
Now you're white!

939
00:47:13,000 --> 00:47:15,500
Lucy have you
eaten anything today?

940
00:47:18,500 --> 00:47:20,700
Have a drink.
Finish that.

941
00:47:21,500 --> 00:47:24,600
-How could l believe such a liar.
-l'm weak!

942
00:47:28,300 --> 00:47:29,800
What's wrong?

943
00:47:30,000 --> 00:47:32,300
You'd think he dumped you.

944
00:47:32,500 --> 00:47:35,500
-You feel bad, but can handle it.
-Air!

945
00:47:35,800 --> 00:47:38,000
l'm in shock today, but...

946
00:47:39,100 --> 00:47:40,800
l want to speak to Fay.

947
00:47:40,900 --> 00:47:43,500
lt's Harry Block. l've been trying
to reach her.

948
00:47:44,000 --> 00:47:46,800
No, it's an emergency.
l gotta talk...

949
00:47:47,000 --> 00:47:50,400
Tell her to call me back.
lt's the car number.

950
00:47:50,600 --> 00:47:51,900
Yes. The car!

951
00:47:52,100 --> 00:47:55,200
-She's in love with someone else.
-This guy is too old for her.

952
00:47:55,500 --> 00:47:56,800
Younger than you.

953
00:47:57,000 --> 00:47:59,600
l'm much too old for her.
lt's ridiculous.

954
00:47:59,800 --> 00:48:03,500
-But my immaturity makes me boyish.
-ls it much longer, Dad?

955
00:48:03,700 --> 00:48:06,100
-We just got done at the fair.
-You're speeding.

956
00:48:06,300 --> 00:48:09,000
-About how much longer is it?
-lt won't be long.

957
00:48:09,300 --> 00:48:12,300
Okay, my sister lives
ten minutes from here.

958
00:48:12,600 --> 00:48:14,400
We'll surprise her.
lt'll be fun.

959
00:48:14,600 --> 00:48:17,000
-You can eat and walk around.
-She's your half-sister.

960
00:48:17,200 --> 00:48:19,400
But it'll still be 10 minutes...

961
00:48:19,600 --> 00:48:21,800
not 5, 'cause she's
a half-sister.

962
00:48:26,500 --> 00:48:27,600
lt's wonderful!

963
00:48:28,800 --> 00:48:30,300
-lt is so funny.
-Do you think?

964
00:48:30,600 --> 00:48:32,200
-And it's so sad.
-You're so sweet.

965
00:48:32,500 --> 00:48:33,300
l love it.

966
00:48:33,500 --> 00:48:35,600
You're so great.
You're so kind to me.

967
00:48:35,900 --> 00:48:38,900
You have such a sweet,
kind instinct.

968
00:48:39,800 --> 00:48:41,500
Don't do that.

969
00:48:42,100 --> 00:48:44,300
l count on you
to be critical...

970
00:48:44,600 --> 00:48:47,600
to really be tough.
You're too easy on me.

971
00:48:47,800 --> 00:48:49,200
What's wrong with this?

972
00:48:49,400 --> 00:48:51,300
What's wrong is that it had...

973
00:48:51,600 --> 00:48:53,100
it had no energy.

974
00:48:53,600 --> 00:48:55,200
l became discouraged with it.

975
00:48:55,700 --> 00:48:58,100
lt doesn't release any power.
lt's nothing.

976
00:48:58,400 --> 00:49:00,900
l thought it was really touching.

977
00:49:01,300 --> 00:49:04,300
You knew when the boy grew up
he would never learn to love.

978
00:49:05,000 --> 00:49:06,800
l think your problem is...

979
00:49:07,000 --> 00:49:09,300
that you love too easily,
and too much.

980
00:49:09,600 --> 00:49:12,300
l think you're beautiful,
and great...

981
00:49:12,700 --> 00:49:15,200
and too kind to me, and lovely.

982
00:49:16,100 --> 00:49:18,200
But you're not in love with me.

983
00:49:18,500 --> 00:49:21,700
l told you not to fall
in love with me.

984
00:49:22,200 --> 00:49:25,100
But still haven't
figured out why.

985
00:49:25,900 --> 00:49:29,100
Why? Because l'm the boy
in that story...

986
00:49:29,400 --> 00:49:30,800
and l can't love.

987
00:49:31,300 --> 00:49:33,200
So, l don't want you to
get into anything.

988
00:49:33,500 --> 00:49:35,100
You love Hilly.

989
00:49:35,800 --> 00:49:36,900
What?

990
00:49:37,200 --> 00:49:38,600
You love Hilly.

991
00:49:41,200 --> 00:49:42,900
Sure. l love Hilly.

992
00:49:43,200 --> 00:49:46,000
He's my son. lt's easy to love
a little kid.

993
00:49:46,900 --> 00:49:48,400
You love music.

994
00:49:49,000 --> 00:49:50,900
And you love baseball.

995
00:49:51,200 --> 00:49:54,400
Baseball's also easy,
because it has rules, foul lines...

996
00:49:54,700 --> 00:49:56,900
but women are complicated.

997
00:49:59,500 --> 00:50:00,600
Happy birthday.

998
00:50:00,900 --> 00:50:02,100
You're kidding!

999
00:50:02,400 --> 00:50:03,500
Come on, open it up.

1000
00:50:04,700 --> 00:50:07,400
You didn't have to
get me anything.

1001
00:50:07,700 --> 00:50:09,400
Another sweater, right?

1002
00:50:11,200 --> 00:50:14,400
A baseball signed by
the 1951 Giants.

1003
00:50:14,600 --> 00:50:16,400
Really! That's so great!

1004
00:50:16,900 --> 00:50:18,700
Bobby Thomson!

1005
00:50:19,000 --> 00:50:21,600
They were the one genuine miracle
of my lifetime!

1006
00:50:21,900 --> 00:50:23,600
When he hit that home run...

1007
00:50:23,800 --> 00:50:26,900
it was the only hint l've had
there may be a God.

1008
00:50:29,300 --> 00:50:30,900
What made you think of it?

1009
00:50:31,500 --> 00:50:33,100
lt was easy.

1010
00:50:35,000 --> 00:50:36,600
You are the greatest.

1011
00:50:36,800 --> 00:50:38,900
lt's your birthday,
so you get awish.

1012
00:50:39,200 --> 00:50:42,300
Anything at all that'll make
your day special.

1013
00:50:43,600 --> 00:50:46,600
You are the greatest.
l don't deserve you.

1014
00:50:47,100 --> 00:50:48,200
You're too...

1015
00:50:48,400 --> 00:50:49,500
Too what?

1016
00:50:57,500 --> 00:51:00,200
-We thought we'd stop in to see you.
-Come in!

1017
00:51:00,400 --> 00:51:02,800
This is Richard.
This is Cookie.

1018
00:51:03,200 --> 00:51:05,300
l'm your Aunt Doris.
You won't remember me.

1019
00:51:05,600 --> 00:51:06,900
Remember Uncle Burt?

1020
00:51:07,100 --> 00:51:08,600
You haven't seen him
in awhile.

1021
00:51:08,800 --> 00:51:10,000
lt's been a long while.

1022
00:51:10,200 --> 00:51:13,300
Something to eat?
A cookie or something?

1023
00:51:13,500 --> 00:51:15,000
Come in the kitchen.

1024
00:51:15,700 --> 00:51:18,200
l gotta go to the bathroom.
Where's the john?

1025
00:51:18,600 --> 00:51:21,200
The bathroom! You just go right
through there.

1026
00:51:21,900 --> 00:51:23,700
So, l thought we'd drop in.

1027
00:51:26,800 --> 00:51:29,600
You're the last person
l ever expected to see.

1028
00:51:29,800 --> 00:51:31,500
